    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**New package**: `packages/generator-rest-client/` â€” 10 files total, no existing files modified.\n\n**Architecture**: External generator using `generatorHandler()` from `@prisma/generator-helper`. Prisma spawns `dist/bin.js` as a child process, communicates via JSON-RPC over stdio. On `generate`, the DMMF is parsed to produce a single `rest-client.ts` file with:\n\n- Enum string union types\n- Typed model interfaces (scalar fields)\n- `CreateInput`/`UpdateInput`/`WhereUniqueInput` types per model\n- A fetch-based `PrismaRestClient` class with `findMany`, `findUnique`, `create`, `update`, `delete` per model\n\n**Key design decisions**:\n- Separate `src/bin.ts` (executable) vs `src/index.ts` (library exports)\n- Build uses `adapterConfig` (CJS+ESM) plus a custom bin target with shebang banner\n- `WhereUniqueInput` derived from `@id` / `@@id` / first `@unique` field\n- Relation fields excluded from interfaces (REST payloads are flat)\n- All DMMF scalar types mapped to appropriate TS types (`DateTime` â†’ `string`, `Decimal` â†’ `string`, etc.)",
